Description:
This Vintage SKIRT Linzner Alpine TRACHTEN is a charming piece of clothing in the traditional German - Austrian style (Trachten mode), with blue flowers pattern, which will pair well with a white blouse. It is airy and comfortable, a lovely choice for a summer stroll. The skirt is in excellent vintage condition. 
MATERIAL: 
Skirt: 100 % cotton 
Lining: 100 % polyester
SIZE of the skirt is approximately 46, corresponding to Large (L). 
The size is not visible on the tag. You can find the clothing sizes and size conversions in Europe here: http://goeurope.about.com/cs/shopping/l/bl_clothes_size.htm - just to have an idea, like they say on the page, size conversion isn't an exact science.
Approximate MEASUREMENTS (taken lying flat) are as follows: 
Length from waist to end of skirt: 82 cm - 32.3 inch
Waist: 42 (x2) cm - 16.5 (x2) inch - expandable a little bit to 44 cm (x2) - 17.3 inch
I use this convertor: http://www.manuelsweb.com/in_cm.htm
SHIPPING
I ship internationally. The shipping taxes specified here refer to priority mail. If you are interested in buying this item, please take a moment to read in detail the Policy of my shop. The shipping amounts specified below are the fees of our Postal Service - as they are very high I haven't included any of the handling costs in the shipping price. Upon request, I can provide the buyer with a copy of the receipt for the shipping fee. 
COMBINED SHIPPING - If you're considering buying more than one item, should your purchase fit into one package weighing less than 1 kilogram then the second item could have zero shipping costs. After the package is shipped I will notify you with the exact shipping cost (upon request, I can send a scan of the receipt), and will refund any extra amount of money paid by you at the moment of purchase.
Also, please be sure to check with your local customs for any extra duties or restrictions that may apply to the purchase of vintage clothes. I have no way of knowing the duties or restrictions for every country (for example, the US may have an annual quota for import of textiles), and so I cannot be held responsible if for any reason the buyer should encounter problems with the package at their customs. I can put the item on Reserve until all those details are known (exact shipping cost and local customs info), so there will be no hurry - what is important is that both seller and buyer know exactly what to expect when purchasing an item, and do all that is necessary so that the item will arrive safely to its new owner.
Feel free to message me with any questions, I will be glad to answer all.

Star Wars Ubrickkian Landspeeder 9000 Z001....
Driving through the streets of Mos Eisley in your new landspeeder, you decide to take a break and have a few drinks.  In the parking lot of the Cantina, you see a gleaming Ubrickkian Landspeeder. Mezmerized, you walk up to it.  The bright white cooliant paint glints in the sunlight.  You peer in through one of the windows.  Plush leather upholstery covers the entire interior.  You notice the keys had been left in the ignition.  You try the door.  It swings open.  Would anyone really notice if it dissapeared for a few days (or weeks)?  Probably not. Product name: Swiss Army Leather Ammunition Bag, Beltbag from 1937; Pre-WW2 Era Swiss Army Ammo Pouch / S.Fäh, Benken #2
Description:
This calf-skin leather Swiss military beltbag was designed for Swiss soldiers to carry spare ammo. 
Although Switzerland was neutral during the war, the Swiss Army remained active and was in alert to be ready to protect the country. This beltbag is a silent witness of these turbulent times.
It is from 1937, marked with the date and the maker's mark: "S. Fäh, Sattler, BENKEN". The Swiss cross is also punched to the back panel. 
The ammo-bag measures 7.3" x 3.7" x 1.6" / 18.5cm x 9.5cm x 4cm.
The inner size of one compartment is 3.3" x 3.3" x 1.2" (8.5 x 8.5 x 3cm).
It is in nice vintage condition without damages. It has a warm dark brown color and nice patina. Some scratches and signs of wear are results of the 80 years and the war times. 
It is intact and fully functional, ready to be used. Please see the photos to judge the condition of this wartime piece.

Description:
BOLO PENDANT, SET of 6 Pieces, Shiny Gold Finish, Southwest, Cowboy, Western Wear, Jewelry Findings, Pendant
A Bolo Pendant is normally worn with some type if string tie.....either leather, or some other twisted rope, or ribbon. This bolo pendant has the back frame attached    See photos 2, 3, and 5 for detail. The front side is a modified triangular shape framing a snake shape, or "S" symbol....ready to slide up or down on your string tie. 
Ready for you to design with a decorative tie, or add your own design to the front of the Pendant. This style tie has been traditionally popular in the Southwest and is usually associated with "Western Wear". Wikipedia claims that although a cowboy claimed to have invented the idea in the 1940s....  but Pioneers in the southwest had been wearing them from between 1866 and 1886 ....and it was even a fad in England in the 1950s by "Teddy Boys".

Founded in 1917 by Giuseppe Ratti, Persol is an Italian eyewear company. The name is derived from “per il sole,” which means “for the sun” in Italian. Product name: Cedarwood & Patchouli Deodorant - Organic Deodorant - All Natural Deodorant
Description:
Still using your favorite store-bought, antiperspirant deodorant? Perhaps it's time to think about ditching it. 
Because it most likely contains a host of harmful ingredients, like aluminum, which has been linked to breast cancer, Alzheimer's, bone disorders, and kidney problems, "fragrance", which is a term typically used to mask a chemical cocktail of synthetic scents that can wreak havoc on your endocrine system, sodium laurel sulfate (SLS), a known carcinogen, parabens, which have also been linked to breast cancer and are known endocrine disruptors, and a whole slew of other ingredients that you probably can't even pronounce and do God only knows what to your body. 
Plus, sweating is GOOD for you. It's how the body rids itself of toxins and cools itself down. But what's that? You'd really rather not get a whiff of what smells like an onion that's been left out in the sun all day every time you lift your arms? 
Fear not, my friend. There's a way to combat the pesky pit bacteria that creates that odor. This recipe contains: 
- Organic Coconut Oil: saturated fats in the form of medium chain triglycerides make coconut oil a rich moisturizer. Add in antimicrobial properties, naturally occurring proteins, vitamin E (a known antioxidant), and a host of beneficial fatty acids and coconut oil's reputation as a use-for-everything oil begins to make sense. 
- Organic Arrowroot Starch: a much better thickening agent than cornstarch, because its organic, gmo-free, and minimally processed. 
- Organic Mango Butter: a harder butter than shea or cocoa, and with a higher melting point, this fatty-acid rich butter is a wonderful moisturizer. 
- Beeswax: a thickening, stabilizing additive that lends some hardiness to the product. 
- Baking Soda: prevents fungal growth and fights odor. 
- Organic Patchouli Essential Oil: known for its disinfecting, antifungal, antiseptic, and deodorizing properties, this essential oil is a powerhouse when it comes to combating underarm odor. 
- Organic Cedarwood (Virginia) Essential Oil: this oil not only blends well with (and, let's face it, tones down) patchouli, but because of its own astringent and fungicidal properties, it works in tandem with the patchouli oil to keep you smelling like you just strolled out of a forest. In a GOOD way. 
If you're looking for a different scent combination, we also offer: 
Fir Needle & Lavender Deodorant
https://www.etsy.com/listing/449075680/fir-needle-lavender-deodorant-organic
Lavender, Rosemary & Tea Tree Deodorant
https://www.etsy.com/listing/464255496/lavender-rosemary-tea-tree-deodorant
Packaged in a recycled, recyclable paperboard tube with a compostable label and shipped in recycled, recyclable materials so you can feel good about what's inside AND outside your product. 
**A FEW NOTES**
- This is an all-natural product made with sterilized equipment and no natural or chemical preservatives. For best results, store in a cool, dark place and use within six months of purchase. Make sure to leave the deodorant tightly capped between uses, and use on clean, dry armpits, as adding dirt or water to any preservative-free product could introduce some yucky bacteria into the mix. 
PRO TIP: if a natural product looks or smells off, discontinue use. 
*For external use only. Keep out of reach of children. Discontinue use if irritation occurs. This information has not been evaluated by the FDA. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.

Product name: OLD BOOKS Perfume Oil - Vanilla, Aromatic Woods, Leather, More - Choose From Four Sizes!
Description:
When I was still a hobbyist perfumer, I worked in an old bookshop. More often than not, as soon as a customer walked through the door, they would take a deep breath and comment on the shop's wonderful aroma. The soft vanilla base, the woodsy heart, and a dry, smoky hint of leather in the scent of old books contain the magic to evoke memories of limitless stories and fairy tale endings.
The ghosts of aging wood pulp and the ripening binding materials of the books would slowly float into my clothes and hair during the day. Every evening when I returned home, my husband would pull me close and tell me how I smelled as lovely as a library. It was then that I knew I wanted to capture that fragrance in a bottle
OLD BOOKS was born, and it is now the signature scent of my Literary Classics Perfume Collection. 
This perfume contains only pure, organic essential oils in a carrier of organic rice bran oil. It is 100% vegan, carefully crafted by hand, and it arrives in an amber glass bottle.

Product name: Vegan  Sugar Wax | All Natural Wax Hair removal | Sugaring Wax Kit | Organic | Sticks Included
Description:
Remove your unwanted hairs the natural and organic way.
Sugaring has been around for hundreds of years as an effective and almost pain free hair removal treatment. It is made with only Nature’s ingredients and has no additives, colors, or fragrances. 
Sugaring can be done in AND out of the shower, and there is no need for extra supplies (simply use the sticks provided or your hands!)
Some benefits include:
-	All natural ingredients
-	Made to order—ALWAYS!
-	Slower and thinner hair growth
-	Smoother skin
-	No ingrown hairs!
Simply reheat the wax in 10 second increments, apply in direction opposite of growth at a malleable temperature, and pull away.
************************************************************************************
Occasionally, clients may experience inflammation after waxing. It can be from small and itchy bumps, to mosquito-bite-like welts. The hives only last a brief time, an hour at most. 
This is called a histamine reaction. The body is reacting to the hairs being pulled out and perceiving the hair removal as a threat. The immune system springs into action producing histamine to fight the threat, like an allergic reaction. 
To calm inflammation, follow up with a skin soother like aloe vera, rose water, or salt water. The inflammation should only last an hour or two before it is completely gone. 
************************************************************************************

Product name: Begleri Worry Beads Black Paracord Skill Toy Fidget Toy Stress Toy
Description:
**With marbles this set weighs .66 ounces or 19 grams. With steel bearings this set weighs 1.17 ounces or 33 grams. Which one you choose is totally up to you. I've heard that heavier is easier to learn for newcomers since it doesn't spin around as fast and you have more control and momentum when it gets going. I personally use marbles in mine, but that may be because i'm an expert and like the speed and lightness.**
You'll receive 1 handmade black paracord begleri. Be sure to tell me how long you want the cord in between the beads in the length portion. Look at the last photo. You'll see that the length of my fingers together is 3 inches. For short game, measure yours and add 1.5 inches. For long game, add 3 inches to what you get. That's how I personally measure. Some already have their own way. Long game is definitely more versatile when it comes to tricks, while short game is easier to learn and the beads clack more. Searching YouTube for 'begleri tricks' will yield more long game tricks being found.
About Begleri
Begleri also known as worry beads, are used for relaxation, passing of time, and just overall enjoyment. They originated in Greece where cab drivers would flip them to limit smoking, and pass time while waiting on customers. For me they really do ease a worried mind.
Shipping

10% of all sale prices will be donated to PSC Partners Seeking A Cure.  PSC Partners Seeking A Cure is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit foundation, whose mission is to provide education and support to PSC patients, families and caregivers and to raise funds to research causes, treatments and cures for Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis.  This disease causes the bile ducts, inside and outside the liver, to become scarred, narrowed and eventually blocked.  As more ducts are blocked, bile becomes trapped in the liver, causing damage.  If left unchecked, liver cell death can result, leading to cirrhosis and the possibility of a liver transplant.  A friend received a PSC diagnosis in 2011, and this organization has been a huge asset for her and her family since that time.  More information about PSC Partners Seeking A Cure and Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis can be found at the organization’s website, http://www.pscpartners.org.

Product name: Believe in yourself... Seller handbook, How to sell online pdf guide, How to sell on Etsy, How to sell items ebook, Quit your day job
Description:
What if creating beauty and living from your passion became your daily reality? What would you be feeling? How would it affect your life? How would the fact of you successfully and fruitfully following your dream affect the lives of your loved ones?
I am truly convinced there is one key difference between successful and less successful artists, crafters and designers, and it is not their artistic talents, nor their ability to take perfect photos or master their tags and titles, even though these are of course important too. What really distinguishes the two is the level of belief and self-confidence that the successful sellers had about themselves even before they became successful. I believe the sellers you look up to often had their success guaranteed even before they actually opened their stores. Why? Because they believed they would be successful. And when they did, the whole world had no choice but to believe it too.
I have written this ebook because I have been where you are. I had my weeks of doubt and anxiety that all the work I have put in creating my artist dream was just a waste of time. But then I decided to change my thinking and once I did, everything else changed too. I want to share with you what I have learned in the process. This ebook has two purposes only: reminding you that you are capable of achieving anything you desire and showing you in practice how to do it through changing your attitude.
Format: pdf (digital file)
Pages: 20
Edition: 2012
Content: inspirational ebook ebout believing in yourself as successful artist, crafter or designer
Delivery: immediate download
Some reviews from my lovely readers:
"I read the book yesterday and I can honestly say it is a gem of a book. I believe that it will be a great guide and tool for those looking to create success for themselves. You take some truths that are timeless and put them in a great format. I love the way you give an overview and then break it down, piece by piece with a personal touch. You have given a personal look into the how and why, and that's what makes your guide unique. It may be a new premise for some but I think that you have brought it to them in a "don't sweat the small stuff" way. You show them how to open up to the fun side of creating and being prosperous; to use their minds as they were meant to be used. I've read about this before and have experienced it myself to some extent - I "forget" to practice it. Your book is concise and yet full of words to help me stay on track. 
Great read!!! I would recommended it to all who are looking for success, no matter what that means to each one."
"I read your ebook twice! First of all I love all the inspirational quotes in between the lines!
I think what you say is really true, in the end, after everyting possible is done and still nothing sells, it comes down to believing in your art and self! This is my biggest hurdle and your ebook really reflected it to me (...) Very inspring and I probably will read it again, just to remind myself of all the good tools you show."

Product name: Sale--Speech Therapy Stimuli Book for Childhood Speech Disorders
Description:
Speech Therapy Stimuli Book for Childhood Speech Disorders
This resource developed for speech-language pathologists and parents gives careful attention to sound and word selection and is presented in an engaging picture format.   This publication incorporates many words considered part of a core vocabulary, which is described as “a small set of basic words in any language that are used frequently and across contexts” (Cross, et al., 1997).  Targeting core vocabulary words helps children to be better understood by others.
The words have been selected carefully to represent a core vocabulary as well as the opportunity to incorporate the following goals:
•	Vowel differentiation/ accuracy 
•	Target voicing errors
•	Sequencing sounds with increasing complexity in one, two, and three syllable words
•	Building intraoral air pressure 
•	Sound placement
•	Developmental acquisition- incorporating “early 8” and “middle 8” sounds  (Shriberg, 1993)
•	Prosody and coarticulation
•	Vocabulary - many first words; high-frequency words
•	Narrative skills- story-based pictures
This book is a useful tool to use in therapy and home practice as part of a treatment program for children with speech sound disorders such as children with hearing loss, childhood apraxia of speech, cleft palate, dysarthria, and phonological impairments.
The book is approximately 22 pages and spiral bound.
ABOUT THE AUTHOR
Becky S. Baas, M.A., CCC-SLP is a pediatric speech-language pathologist with15 years of experience working with children with communication disorders in school and medical settings.   Becky has worked since 2005 in the pediatric practice at Mayo Clinic, Rochester, Minnesota. Her clinical and research interests are in the areas of early language acquisition, hearing impairment and cochlear implantation, speech disorders related to craniofacial anomalies, and evaluation and treatment of motor speech disorders in children. Her treatment approach uses evidence-based techniques incorporating practical, functional goals which enhance motivation for the child as well as caregivers. 
ABOUT THE ILLUSTRATORS
Jim Bertram and his daughter, Marissa, share a love for art.  His award-winning cartoons have appeared in Highlights for Children, The Wall Street Journal, Reader's Digest and Best Editorial Cartoons of the Year.  Jim's artwork is available for purchase at CartoonStock.com
Marissa expanded her art education into digital media where she owns and operates the content creation company, Dogsbody Pictures LLC
Upon payment, your book is mailed promptly within 2 days of purchase.

Product name: Poetic Justice Volume One: Poems from Incarcerated Women in Oklahoma
Description:
Poetic Justice is a nonprofit 501(c)3 organization with the purpose of offering a positive, constructive form of self-expression to those affected by incarceration. We accomplish this purpose through offering writing classes that humanize and empower those at-risk of incarceration, currently incarcerated, or previously incarcerated. Poetic Justice is comprised of an all volunteer, all female staff who seek to help develop the voices of women who have found their voices lost, forgotten, or unheard. All proceeds directly fund our program.
Oklahoma has the highest incarceration rate of women in the world. For every 100,000 women, 132 in Oklahoma will be incarcerated with the national average at only 68. 
"Poetic Justice Volume 1" is a collection of poems from incarcerated women throughout the state of Oklahoma that detail their life experiences and emotional fortitude.

Product name: Custom WEDDING CHARM photo memory soldered glass personalized charms reversible with your 2 pictures or images toss bouquet boutonniere
Description:
This is a listing for ONE custom silver memory charm that I will make to order for you! Have a favorite picture of a loved one, pet, friend, or saying? This adorable charm measures approximately 1" square, and features a reversible design. You will email me one or 2 photos of your choosing and I will custom make the item for you! These are not those cheesy glue on commercial style frames. All is sandwiched together between two pieces of glass, sealed inside and soldered with lead-fr*ee silver solder. I can make your photo as is color or even change it to sepia or black & white. I will shrink it and crop it for you to fit the pendant. Want one side to have a special sentiment...I can do that too! I am pretty flexible with the design...so let me know what you want and we will work it out! Possibilities are ENDLESS! This will be beautiful hanging from your bouquet or for a toss bouquet, and will last as a momento for years to come!  Need a different quantity?  The listing is for one, but I can make any number you need, just add the quantity to your cart. PLEASE READ THE FAQ SECTION BELOW TO ANSWER THE MOST COMMON QUESTIONS!!!! :)
Makes a wonderful gift! Don't forget to get one for the groom's boutonniere too!
These generally take about a week or less to ship once the photos have been proofed.  
The photo shows what your charms may look like when hung on your own ribbon. Yours comes with just the charms ordered.
Email images to  tstept2 [!at] aol.com or attach to a convo.  THANKS!
------------------------
FAQ:
------------------------
1. How long will they take before I get my charms?
Once photos are proofed, I have them ready to ship in about a week or less usually.  During busy holiday seasons, it can be up to 3 weeks.  I do my very best to get them out as quick as humanly possible, and please let me know if you have special time constraints, so we can upgrade to faster shipping, etc.  
2.  Where do I send my photos? 
Please email the photos in their original uncropped form to  tstept2 [!at] aol.com or attach to an etsy convo, and I will crop, edit, resize and email back a proof for you in color, b&w and sepia.  
3.  How big do photos need to be?
Atleast 1" in size, the larger the better!
4.  What goes on the backside?
Anything you wish!  I can place the same photo, another photo, a word, a text, initial, date, a pretty print I can create, you name it!  Let me know what you wish to have, and I can create it for you!
5.  Can I mail photos instead?
Nope.  I really prefer scanned images, as it is really scary to mail precious photos, and I cannot be responsible for the post office.  I would HATE for your photos to be lost!  Scanning pics is best...or even a friend or coworker, or copy shop can scan them.  I have even created these with pictures of photos!  :)
6.  Can I get the blank charm to add my own photo?
These are not commercially made pop on charms.  I create these from scratch right around your photos, so sadly it is not possible.  I cannot ship without the photos.  
7.  I need my charm within a REALLY tight timeframe, like a week or less...is this possible?
YES!!!  I do offer rush processing, which is a 10 fee per item, and I have it ready to ship in about 24 hours from the okay of the photo proof.  You may still want to upgrade to priority or express, but I only charge exact shipping, so US priority is 5.50 to anywhere in the US, and express next day is 18.50.  I do it all the time, and if we act fast, you will have your very special charm right on time for the big day :)  I have a separate listing in my shop for RUSH charms.
8.  I am worried my photo may not work, should I send it prior to ordering?
Nope.   Please do not send pics until you place the order.  I do not do any photo editing etc until you place the order.  I have not turned a photo away in over a decade of creating these, so rest assured, I will make it work :)

And the flowers last almost forever instead of a couple of days.

Product name: Beach Hut Personalised Wedding Post Box / Hand-made Wedding Card Box
Description:
This beach hut wedding post box is perfect for those who love the British seaside, offering a unique place for guests to leave cards on your special day. The fabulous beach hut wedding post box will be an unusual talking point on your wedding day. It will provide a feature point for your guests to deposit their cards and, being made from real wood, it is sturdy enough to be used as a storage or keepsake box after the event.
It has a large slot in the front allowing for easy posting and the lid lifts off to access the cards inside.
The beach hut wedding post box is available with a base colour of Grace White or Ivory and a wide range of contrast choices (please images for a full list) so there's sure to be something to suit. You can also choose 2 further colours for the bunting (this will also be used for the bucket, spade and ring). The plaque above the door can be personalised with up to 2 lines of text containing a maximum of 12 characters on each line and the date of the wedding can be added to the bunting too, making the box even more special and personal. Select the beach hut stripe colours from our options and then just add a "Note to Seller" at the checkout with your required personalisation and bunting colours.
Further personalisation options and more colours can be arranged but if you need these services then please ask prior to placing an order. Some of these extra options may incur an additional cost.
PLEASE NOTE that all items are individually handmade and personalised to order by us in our Lincolnshire workshop and each one takes time to produce so delivery will usually be within 28 days.
But this does mean that your box will be created especially for you and delivered by courier to your chosen address. We hate to disappoint so please allow plenty of time between ordering and delivery.
If you need delivery sooner then please contact us before placing an order and we might be able to help.
We ship by courier so a  signature is usually required but delivery to an alternative address or neighbour is acceptable.
Materials:
Every personalised wedding post box is carefully handmade, by us here at Lindleywood, from high-grade sustainable European pine supplied by a small local wood-merchant. It is then hand-painted with hard-wearing water-based wood paints. These paints, by Little Greene, a small independent British manufacturer from the northwest of England (who have been creating high quality paints since 1773), enable us to create beautiful products. The paints comply with European Standard BS EN 71-3:1995 (better known as the 'Toy Paint Regulations') so are safe for children too.
Important Note regarding colours: The colours shown on our paint chart are the colours we have available as standard. Please note that although we have tried to accurately portray these colours, Internet browsers and screens may cause colours to appear slightly differently.
Please be aware that each item is individually hand-made and hand-painted to order by us so one item will differ slightly from another and may not appear exactly as in the photographs of other products. This means that each product is entirely unique and extremely individual! Also note that as we make each item from wood there may some variation in grain. Over time there may also be movement in joints and surfaces. This is down to the nature of ‘real wood' as opposed to synthetic materials and we feel further adds to the individuality of each product.
Size:
The campervan wedding post box measures approximately 60cm (h) x 41cm (w) x 38cm (d).

✔️WHAT'S THE HAT MADE OF?
These custom mini sombreros are constructed much in the same way that my mini top hats are.  They start with a buckram frame with hat wire sewn into the brim.  The top crown is wet shaped and then air dried to hardened and then attached to the brim.  I hand sew all sequins and embroidery thread.  The pom pom fringe is sewn around the brim, and then tulle/ribbon and feathers are added.   A felt pocket has been sewn into the bottom for a headband to fit though and looping added for other hair attachments(combs, bobby pins, clips).  An elastic band has been added for easy, ready to wear fun!
❗️❗️❗️Send me a note during checkout if you'd like other hair attachments added free of charge
✔️MEASUREMENTS & WEIGHT
6 inches in diameter by 3 inches tall

These fancy little hats will be the life of any party....BACHELORETTE, WEDDINGS, COSPLAY, THEMED BIRTHDAY PARTIES, OFFICE PARTIES, or just going out on the town! You name it!

The Lucky Sixpence was originally to be given to the bride from her father and placed in her left shoe. He did this to wish her all the blessings a father can give to his daughter. It was to symbolize good health for the couple as well as great wealth. Most important is was to ensure his daughter happiness. It is then typically passed down from generation to generation in a family.
Today the Wedding Sixpence is given to the bride from many sources. It is a popular bridal shower gift, a lovely gift from the bride's father, and is also a keepsake and family heirloom handed down from mother to daughter or father to daughter.

Description:
| New Stencil that is ready to be used! This is not a sign! |
*Looking to buy Pallet Signs? Check out Secondtimeco! 
Create custom projects with this stencil you can customize! 
Art design by Detroit Stencils. Professionally cut from quality 7 mil mylar sheeting, reusable. Stencil material is clear. 
Be sure to take a look at our line of Stencils!! We're adding more daily and look forward to working with you on your special project! 
http://www.etsy.com/shop/DetroitStencils
New to Stenciling? ( Here is some tips! )
Stenciling Tip 1: Use a Professional Tool
Stenciling brushes are round with short, stiff bristles. Use it in a quick up-and-down movement to dab paint onto your stencil. This helps prevent paint getting under the edges. A sponge or small roller works well too.
Stenciling Tip 2: Work from The Outside
Start panting on the edges of the stencil, working into the center, rather than from the center outwards. Again this helps prevent paint getting under the edges as you're less likely to accidentally bump the brush against an edge.
Stenciling Tip 3: Less is More
Don't overload a brush with paint as it'll seep under the edges of the stencil. Load the brush lightly, so that the ends of the bristles are covered evenly; wipe off any excess on a piece of paper or cloth.
Stenciling Tip 4: Think Thin
You'll get better results by applying two thin coats rather than one thick one.Wait for the first to dry before applying the second.
Stenciling Tip 5: Get Sticky
Keep a stencil in place by taping it at the top and bottom with a piece of tape. Low-tack tape is best as it's very easy to remove and shouldn't pull off any paint from the surface.
Stenciling Tip 6: Go Multi-Colored
To use more than one color in a stencil, use tape to mask off areas of the stencil you don't want in a particular color.
Stenciling Tip 7: Practice Makes Perfect
If you're using various stencils together, first try it out on a piece of paper. It's far easier to find out that something isn't working at this stage and then correct it than when you're painting on your final surface.
Stenciling Tip 8: Wash Regularly
Not you, your stencil! If you're doing a repeat design, wash your stencil regularly in warm water to keep the edges free of paint. If there's some paint on an edge, you won't get a crisp edge to your painted stencil.
Stenciling Tip 9: Store stencils Flat
A stencil, obviously, needs to be flat to be usable. To stop it from buckling, put it between two pieces of card and store it somewhere flat, such as in a book or telephone directory.

I will design your geofilter as you request and email it to you within the next 48 hours (though usually sooner). Then during that date and time anyone in the area you selected will be able to use your filter on Snapchat!
Uploading a custom filter to Snapchat is an additional expense to consider. Prices vary depending on size of location and duration. A 20,000 square foot area and 8-hour time period is 5 (the minimum dollar amount). This would cover almost all weddings. If you want your geofilter to apply to two different locations (for example in the ceremony area and a separate reception area) you will need to set two separate geofilters. Uploading your filter is a simple & quick process that you complete online with your Snapchat account. I will provide more detailed instructions on this with the delivery of your image file. Here is more information on Snapchat's On-Demand Geofilter program: https://support.snapchat.com/en-US/co/on-demand-geofilters

Description:
String lights with 100 fairy lights on copper or silver wire.

https://www.etsy.com/listing/481362289/remote-controlled-lights-100-fairy?ref=shop_home_active_4
This product is a string of 100 warm white Fairy Lights (also called starry lights) on a thin copper wire that is powered by 3 AA batteries, 3 C Batteries, or a wall plug. 
This item is small and great for enhancing home decor and party decor crafts. This product comes in copper or silver wire color.  There are 100 Warm White Fairy Lights on each strand, and the strands are 16.5-feet long. (5 meters)
The AA Battery Packs are roughly 2.9" by 1.9" by 0.75".  They have one timer setting for 6 hours on and 18 hours off, and they have a steady-on setting where there is no timer.
The AA Pack and Waterproof AA Pack are hard-wired.  The other battery packs and wires are connected with our plug system.  The plug system allows you to change wires, change battery packs, and expand to more lights if you need to add lights.
The Waterproof AA Packs are rough 3.3" by 2.5" by 0.9".  They have one timer setting for 6 hours on and 18 hours off, and they have a steady-on setting where there is no timer.
The C Battery pack is 3.3" by 3.3" by 1.5".  It uses 3 C batteries.  The battery box is clear, and it is not waterproof.  The box one timer setting for 6 hours on and 18 hours off. There is also a steady-on setting where there is no timer. C batteries will last about 5 times as long as AA batteries.
The USB option plugs into any USB port.  This product has 7 feet of lead wire, and a remote control.  You can power these lights with your computer, your laptop, your car, or best of all with a wall plug that has a USB port.  (Select the plug-in option if you want us to provide the wall plug.)  For our non-USA, non-Canada customers, this would be your best option if you want plug-in lights.  Just add a local USB power plug to this product, and you are good to go!
The plug-in option uses 110V AC power. It uses an American style plug attached to the USB product described in the previous paragraph.  There are 2 USB ports on each plug-in module.  This plug-in option is not designed for outdoor use.  You can operate 2 sets of USB lights from one plug-in and with one remote.
When the timers are set, the lights come on at the same time each day. Batteries are not included with the batter pack options.
Battery life varies due to the brand and the environment, but quality AA alkaline batteries will last 15 to 20 days under normal circumstances.  C batteries will last 60 to 90 days.  *All run times are with the timer set.

Product name: Waterless Airlock for wide mouth mason jar lacto fermenting 3 pack
Description:
NEW 3 pack of Fermie Friend Waterless Airlocks for large mouth mason jar fermenting (JARS ARE NOT INCLUDED). 100% food grade silicone, non-toxic, BPA-Free, and dishwasher safe.
The lid fits onto any U.S. wide mouth mason jar (like Ball, Mason or Kerr). Attach the lid to any wide mouth mason jar - fits a half-gallon jar for larger batches and small half pint wide mouth jars.
Ferment just about any vegetable in a wide mouth mason jar.
The one piece silicone waterless airlock design allows for gasses that are created during fermentation to be vented out of the top of the lid while keeping air out of the container.
Lacto-fermentation is the process by which lactic acid bacteria metabolize vegetable sugars and create lactic acid and carbon dioxide. The process is completely vegan and should not be confused with the word “lactose,” which refers to milk sugar.
Sauerkraut is made by a process called lacto-fermentation that is analogous to how traditional (not heat-treated) pickled cucumbers and kimchi are made. The cabbage is finely shredded, layered with salt and left to ferment in a wide mouth mason jar with an airlock.

Product name: 45 Recycled Glass Beads African Glass Beads - 14mm Clear Aqua Beads - Sea Glass - Jewelry Making Supplies - Made in Ghana (RCY-RND-AQU-649)
Description:
These great beads are made by the Krobo People of Ghana, Africa. Powder glass beads are made by crushing glass to a fine powder and heating it so that the particles fuse together. The glass is then poured into clay molds, with a cassava leaf stem used to make the hole. They are baked in an oven and the glass fuses and the cassava stem burns up. This technique has been used in Africa for centuries.
Bead Size: 14mm diameter
Strand Length: 24"
Approximate # of Beads: 45
Hole Size: 3mm

Product name: Hemp Music Bracelet - 3 in 1 Treble Clef and Eighth Note Charm Bracelet
Description:
ABOUT THIS BRACELET:
This lovely charm bracelet is like wearing three bracelets, with only one piece of jewelry! Silver toned "8th note" and "treble clef" charms are woven on to colored hemp with a casual braid between them.  Your bracelet will be made-to-order, just for you!
HEMP COLOR: Choose one from the list of colors. The featured color in the main picture is gray. Examples of the other colors are in the last picture. If you'd like your bracelet to be a combination of 2 (or 3 or 4!) please select "combo of 2" in the color menu and send me a message to specify the color request, either before or after purchasing.
SIZE: 
This bracelet can be made in any size you want! Please include your measurement in the "note to seller" box upon check out. If no size is specified, then I will make it in the most common size, 6" expandable.
Is this a gift for someone else and you don't know their size? Not a problem, my bracelets are all adjustable via pull cords. For example, a 6" bracelet will be 6" around when fully tightened. But there is about 4"-5" of cord left over for the bracelet to expand upon. This way, someone with an 8" wrist could still wear a 6" bracelet, but someone with a 5" wrist may find it to be too big. If deciding between 2 sizes, go for the smaller size: bracelets can expand to be bigger, but can't be reduced any smaller than the stated size.
ABOUT FIT:
Please note, this bracelet is designed to be a fitted bracelet so that the 3 parts stay put. If the bracelet is worn too loosely the charms may overlap (which doesn't look as cool!) So if your wrist is any smaller than 6", please let me know so I can make sure your bracelet is an appropriate fit for you :)
Rough Size Guide:
(XXS) 4"-4.5" is for children
(XS) 5"-5.5" is typical for older children, teens, and smaller framed women
(S) 6"-6.5" is the most common size request I receive, fits smaller men and small to average women
(M) 7"-7.5" is the most common size for average sized men, also for average to larger women
(L) 8"-8.5 is for larger women and average to large men
(XL) 9" is an uncommon size, but requested a handful of times for larger men
Reference points:
Female: 5'3, 105 lbs = 5.5"
Male: 6', 200lbs = 7"
